## Test Cases

### TC-001: Empty Email and Password
| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **TC ID** | TC-001 |
| **Title** | Verify login fails when both email and password fields are left empty |
| **Preconditions** | User is on the login page (https://app.vwo.com/#/login) |
| **Steps** | 1. Navigate to the login page.<br>2. Leave the "Email address" field empty.<br>3. Leave the "Password" field empty.<br>4. Click the "Sign in" button. |
| **Expected Result** | Login should fail and an error message "Your email, password, IP address or location did not match" (or field validation error) should be displayed. |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Category** | Negative |
| **Spec File** | `login.spec.ts` |

### TC-002: Invalid Email Format
| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **TC ID** | TC-002 |
| **Title** | Verify login fails when an invalid email format is entered |
| **Preconditions** | User is on the login page |
| **Steps** | 1. Navigate to the login page.<br>2. Enter an invalid email format (e.g., "invalid_email_format") in the "Email address" field.<br>3. Enter a dummy password (e.g., "Password123!") in the "Password" field.<br>4. Click the "Sign in" button. |
| **Expected Result** | The system should reject the invalid email format and display an appropriate error message like "Your email, password, IP address or location did not match" or a specific format validation error. |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Category** | Negative |
| **Spec File** | `login.spec.ts` |

